last_episode_to_air.name: Climate Change, The Arctic Ocean
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Go Jetters are at the top of the world, helping Professor Wave research polar bears in the Arctic Ocean. Climate change is causing the polar bear's ice home to melt away. Although they get to see a wild polar bear called Kalik, trouble strikes when Foz and Kyan waste too much energy on heat and run down the ship's power! With a chunk of melting ice heading towards them, the Go Jetters see the perils caused by climate change first hand, and they spring into action to find a way to save the ship.

name: Go Jetters
overview: Go Jetters follows the adventures of four plucky international heroes, Xuli, Kyan, Lars and Foz, as they travel the globe with their friend and mentor Ubercorn, a disco-dancing unicorn. Together they save the world's most famous landmarks from the mischievous meddlings of their nemesis, Grandmaster Glitch.

seasons.name: Series 1
seasons.overview:
Go Jetter cadets Xuli, Kyan, Lars and Foz are in their senior year at the Go Jet Academy, taking part in the final, and best part of their training: the around the world field trip! Joined by their mentor, Ubercorn, the Go Jetters travel the world in JetPad, learning as much as they can about the locations they visit.

But, not all is well, as Academy flunk-out Grandmaster Glitch also travels the world, creating mayhem and havoc in every place he ends up, whether he means to or not. Alongside his Grimbots, they travel the world in rustbucket Grim HQ.

When Glitch is up to no-good, it's up to the Go Jetters to save the day, using their geographical knowledge, and skills they've learned in training.

seasons.name: Series 2
seasons.overview:
Go Jetters Xuli, Kyan, Lars and Foz are back, and better than ever! Still travelling the world with their mentor Ubercorn, and stopping even bigger glitches than before. Grandmaster Glitch and his Grimbots have nothing on them!

The Go Jetters continue their training as cadets, now helping to do even more on the tropical island archipelago known as the Go Jet Academy. From testing brand new Click-Ons, to helping to train new cadets, the schedule for these heroes is more packed than ever before! But, even if they're at the academy, they're still learning, whether it be about natural disasters, geographical concepts, or even how certain energy is generated!

seasons.name: Series 3
seasons.overview: The Go Jetters are back, for all new adventures! Join Xuli, Kyan, Lars, Foz and new cadet Tala as they travel the world with their disco-grooving mentor, Ubercorn and foil the plans of Grandmaster Glitch and his cheeky Grimbots.

episodes.name: The Eiffel Tower, France
episodes.overview: Meet the Go Jetters, four explorers on a global adventure! In this animated adventure comedy series, plucky heroes Xuli, Kyan, Lars and Foz travel the world with their teacher, Ubercorn - a disco-loving unicorn. In France, Grandmaster Glitch breaks the Eiffel Tower when he uses it as a TV aerial. Can the Go Jetters fix it?

episodes.name: The Pyramids of Giza, Egypt
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch creates trouble with a little pyramid when he and the Go Jetters visit Egypt.

episodes.name: Stonehenge, England
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch decides to play giant dominoes with Stonehenge stones. Can the Go Jetters stop him?

episodes.name: The Sahara Desert, Africa
episodes.overview: When building a sandcastle around an oasis, Glitch threatens the safety of the touaregs and their camels.

episodes.name: Niagara Falls, Canada and USA
episodes.overview: Glitch blocks Niagara Falls to give Grim HQ a mud bath causing a hydroelectric power station to stop working.

episodes.name: Sydney Opera House, Australia
episodes.overview: Glitch steals the Sydney Opera House to compete in a yacht race.

episodes.name: The Statue of Liberty, USA
episodes.overview: Glitch decides to make the Statue of Liberty look like him, he also makes it fall right into the path of a passing ferry.

episodes.name: The Brandenburg Gate, Germany
episodes.overview: Glitch steals the Quadriga of the Brandenburg Gate to make himself a Carousel.

episodes.name: Lambert-Fisher Glacier, Antarctica
episodes.overview: Glitch threatens the Lambert Glacier while he is making an ice statue of himself.

episodes.name: Chichen Itza, Mexico
episodes.overview: Glitch's giant ball game threatens El Castillo, Chichen Itza.

episodes.name: The Great Wall of China
episodes.overview: Glitch and his Grimbots have a long race on the Great Wall of China.

episodes.name: The Leaning Tower of Pisa, Italy
episodes.overview: The Go Jetter race to fix the Leaning Tower of Pisa, but has it really been glitched?

episodes.name: Lake Titicaca, South America
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch lands with a splash in Lake Titicaca.

episodes.name: The Colosseum, Italy
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch goes to the Colloseum to race his grimbots. Can the Go Jetters stop him?

episodes.name: The Taj Mahal, India
episodes.overview: The grimbots and Glitch attach a bit of the Taj Mahal to Grim HQ.

episodes.name: Mount Etna, Italy
episodes.overview: Glitch makes popcorn in Mount Etna, but he blocks the volcano and endangers the farms on its slopes.

episodes.name: Table Mountain, South Africa
episodes.overview: Glitch wants to ski, so the Grimbots give Table Mountain a snowy peak, which threatens its rare plants.

episodes.name: The Northern Lights, Finland
episodes.overview: Ubercorn is excited to see the Northern Lights but Glitch's Grunge-Grimbler covers them with smoke.

episodes.name: The Amazon Rainforest, South America
episodes.overview: Glitch wants a picnic so he stops the rain in the Amazon rainforest, upsetting the local tree frogs.

episodes.name: The Dead Sea, Middle East
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are relaxing by the Dead Sea when Grandmaster Glitch causes a catastrophe by dumping barrels of custard into the sea.

episodes.name: The Forbidden City, China
episodes.overview: Some runaway Chinese drums roll towards the Forbidden City, and it's up to the Go Jetters stop them.

episodes.name: The Wieliczka Salt Mine, Poland
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters have to save the famous Salt Statues from floods due to Glitch's digging when Glitch is trying to get salt for his chips.

episodes.name: Giant's Causeway, Northern Ireland
episodes.overview: A giant Grandmaster Glitch means big trouble for the Giant's Causeway, but can the Go Jetters help?

episodes.name: The Golden Gate Bridge, USA
episodes.overview: It is a very foggy day, and the Golden Gate Bridge foghorns are missing. Then they find out that Glitch has stolen them to use as horns for his Grimbler. Can the Go Jetters help?

episodes.name: Komodo National Park, Indonesia
episodes.overview: Glitch supersizes a fierce Komodo dragon, and the Go Jetters must find the sizeray to fix the glitch.

episodes.name: Big Ben, England
episodes.overview: Glitch removes Big Ben's bell on New Year's Eve.

episodes.name: The Strokkur Geyser, Iceland
episodes.overview: The geysers in Iceland are blocked. Glitch is to blame and it could cause an earthquake.

episodes.name: The Aqueduct of Segovia, Spain
episodes.overview: Glitch turns Segovia Aqueduct into a giant water slide and the Go Jetters must stop him from toppling it to the ground.

episodes.name: Rio de Janeiro, Brazil
episodes.overview: Glitch has stopped the samba at the Rio carnival. Will they stop him from ruining the carnival?

episodes.name: Mount Everest, Asia
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are enjoying a calm day, apart from Kyan who wants to go on an adventure. He settles on climbing Mount Everest. Grandmaster Glitch is busy working on his mustache and crashes into Mount Everest. The Grimbots play in the snow and are joined by Glitch, who makes a giant snowball which starts rolling down the mountain with him on it. the Go Jetters stop the snowball from hitting some mountaineers by using GO Shield and GO Force. Glitch ends up in the snow but the Grimbots have escaped in GrimHQ and left him cold in the snow. The Go Jetters rescue him and ...

episodes.name: Loch Ness, Scotland
episodes.overview: A Grimbot is spying on the Go Jetters as they read stories about the Loch Ness monster. They all go to Loch Ness. The Go Jetters view a tranquil loch with a fisherman in a boat. All of a sudden the fisherman is dragged along by an unknown creature. He finally lets go of his rod and Xuli, using GO Dive, goes to investigate. She takes a photo and it is Grandmaster Glitch in the Grimbler. Glitch continues to dive towards the bottom hunting for Nessie but the Grimbler begins to break apart and it shoots back to the surface spilling oil. The Go Jetters use GO Grab and GO ...

episodes.name: The Grand Canyon, USA
episodes.overview: Kyan is wire-walking across the Grand Canyon as part of the GO Jetters training. Grandmaster Glitch fires his own wire across the canyon onto the the Grand Canyon Skywalk to try and beat Kyan. Grandmaster Glitch uses magnetic boots to walk across the wire. The Grimbots watch in admiration and play very loud music which causes the wires to vibrate leaving Kyan and Glitch hanging in danger, along with tourists on the Skywalk. Foz and Lars use GO Boots to support the Skywalk and to stop the loud music in the Grimbler. GO Fix is used by Lars to fix the Skywalk. Kyan then ...

episodes.name: Easter Island, Chile
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch is on holiday on the Easter Island. He complains that there are too many tourists taking photos of the Moai statues and disturbing his rest. Glitch gets the Grimbots to build a new statue to distract the tourists but they are not impressed. The Grimbots have built a large pink poodle! Glitch breaks it and the broken pieces roll down a hill towards some tourists. The GO Jetters save them and also save the statues using GO Giant and GO Roll. One final piece of the poodle statue hits Glitch and knocks him off his chair.

episodes.name: The Parthenon, Greece
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch is watching a James Bond film and he loves it. He thinks the only bad thing is that he was not in it. He starts making a film at the Parthenon. The film is based on Glitch beating the Go Jetters. The Grimbots are dressed up as the Go Jetters and Ubercorn and they have a cardboard Vroomster. Glitch wants to make it better and he tricks the Go Jetters by pretending the Grimbler is broken. The Go Jetters come to help and when they are distracted the Grimbots take the Vroomster. They then race around in it and keep knocking into the Parthenon. The Go ...

episodes.name: Saint Basil's Cathedral, Russia
episodes.overview: It is Grandmaster Glitch's birthday. The Grimbots make him a rubbish cake as he wanted one with green icing which looks a little like a castle. The Grimbots cover St Basil's Cathedral in green icing and Glitch loves it. Due to the cold weather the icing sets hard and traps some Cossack dancers inside. The Go Jetters come to help but the Grimbots trapped Lars and Foz in icing. Kyan distracts Glitch by joining some Cossack dancers to perform a birthday dance. Xuli uses GO Force set to heat to rescue Lars and Foz, who join her in melting the icing on the cathedral. It ...

episodes.name: Tarbela Dam, Pakistan
episodes.overview: When Grandmaster Glitch steals the G.O. Force, the forecast isn't good for the Tarbela Dam.

episodes.name: Mount Rushmore, USA
episodes.overview: The Grimbots add Glitch's face to one of the presidents on Mount Rushmore.

episodes.name: Caernarfon Castle, Wales
episodes.overview: In Wales, Glitch makes a lot of noise by using a shield as a musical instrument. How will the Go Jetters retrieve Xuli's treasured 'Academy Ace' flying trophy from Caernarfon Castle?

episodes.name: The Great Barrier Reef, Australia
episodes.overview: The team dives into action as Glitch's treasure hunt endangers the Great Barrier Reef.

episodes.name: Christmas Special: The North Pole, Arctic Ocean
episodes.overview: It's Christmas Eve and Santa's sleigh has vanished - can the Go Jetters save Christmas?

episodes.name: Hong Kong
episodes.overview: Glitch decides to create mini master toys. But they start to munch through everything in Hong Kong.

episodes.name: Waitomo Glowworm Caves, New Zealand
episodes.overview: It's Go Jetters glow when Glitch uses glow worms for his disco pizzazz in New Zealand.

episodes.name: Lake Retba, Senegal
episodes.overview: Glitch wants more strawberry milkshake so the grimbots suck up the pink water of Senegal's Milkshake Lake.

episodes.name: The Paddy Fields of China
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters swing into action when Glitch uses real landmarks for his crazy golf course.

episodes.name: Cappadocia, Turkey
episodes.overview: Glitch's game of hide-and-seek threatens to topple the fairy chimneys of Cappadocia in Turkey.

episodes.name: Maasai Mara National Park, Kenya
episodes.overview: The team roars into action as Glitch tries to take a selfie with a lion in the Maasai Mara.

episodes.name: The Gobi Desert, Mongolia
episodes.overview: Glitch and his grimbots are on the hunt for a super sized skeleton for their Museum of Grim and Gitch's giant drill causes a dino disaster for the team's fossil hunt in the Gobi Desert.

episodes.name: Bioluminescent Bay, Puerto Rico
episodes.overview: Glitch's bath time puts the creatures of Puerto Rico's Bioluminescent Bay in bubble-trouble.

episodes.name: The Blue Mountains, Jamaica
episodes.overview: Trouble brews in Jamaica when Glitch's campfire threatens a coffee plantation.

episodes.name: The Jigokudani Monkey Park, Japan
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters fly to the rescue in Japan, as Glitch is up to his usual monkey business.

episodes.name: The Nazca Lines, Peru
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters race to protect ancient artwork in Peru when Glitch sweeps the desert and erases the Nazca Lines.

1.name: Series 1
1.overview:
Go Jetter cadets Xuli, Kyan, Lars and Foz are in their senior year at the Go Jet Academy, taking part in the final, and best part of their training: the around the world field trip! Joined by their mentor, Ubercorn, the Go Jetters travel the world in JetPad, learning as much as they can about the locations they visit.

But, not all is well, as Academy flunk-out Grandmaster Glitch also travels the world, creating mayhem and havoc in every place he ends up, whether he means to or not. Alongside his Grimbots, they travel the world in rustbucket Grim HQ.

When Glitch is up to no-good, it's up to the Go Jetters to save the day, using their geographical knowledge, and skills they've learned in training.

episodes.name: Petra
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters have to save the ancient city of Petra when Glitch causes an earthquake.

episodes.name: The Matterhorn
episodes.overview: Glitch puts the Go Jetters and other mountaineers in danger when he decides to descend Mount Matterhorn.

episodes.name: Bonneville Salt Flats
episodes.overview: Xuli and Glitch go head to head as they try to beat the Go Jet Academy land speed record.

episodes.name: Rainforests of Sumatra, Indonesia
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters much save the world's stinkiest plant from becoming Glitch's new perfume.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Artificial Reef
episodes.overview: When she finds a shipwreck on a coral reef, Xuli learns that not all glitches need fixing.

episodes.name: Machu Picchu
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters must stop a giant Grimbot bouncing down the valley of Machu Picchu.

episodes.name: Avenue of the Baobabs
episodes.overview: A baby lemur needs rescuing when Glitch's HQ crashes into the baobabs.

episodes.name: Venice
episodes.overview: Glitch turns the Canals of Venice into roads.

episodes.name: Seattle Space Needle
episodes.overview: The team goes where no Go Jetter has gone before, when Glitch tries to launch into space by attaching huge rocket boosters.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Hailstorm
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters join Ubercorn in the Go Jet Academy to try out a brand new super vacuum that reportedly can suck up bad weather. But can it save the Go Jet Academy from a glitched thunderstorm?

episodes.name: Harbin Ice City
episodes.overview: Grim HQ overheats and lands in Harbin Ice City, melting in the process the amazing ice sculptures.

episodes.name: Dover
episodes.overview: The team race to save the White Cliffs of Dover when Glitch digs for classroom chalk.

episodes.name: Central Park, New York
episodes.overview: Glitch visits Broadway while the Go Jetters tackle a huge cloud of smog in Central Park.

episodes.name: Bullet Train, Japan
episodes.overview: Glitch wonders where his grimbots have gone. Some excited bleeps further down a rail platform reveal that they have jumped into the driver's cabin of a bullet train, they steal it and then they press all the buttons.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Wind Power
episodes.overview: When his kite comes to close to the academy's windfarm, the Go Jetters must save Glitch.

episodes.name: Gua Rusa, Borneo
episodes.overview: Glitch scoops up all the guano of Gua Rusa to grow his Halloween pumpkin in just one day.

episodes.name: Christmas Island, Indian Ocean
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters snap into action as Glitch seeks some festive cheer on Christmas Island.

episodes.name: Terracotta Army, China
episodes.overview: Ubercorn shuts down Glitch's raucous rock performance leaving the Grandmaster determined to find a brand new crowd who'll love his loud music. He decides to travel to Chian in China. Can the Go Jetters stop Glitch's noisy guitar and save the Terracotta Army in China?

episodes.name: Panama Canal, Panama
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch is late for the European Moustache of the Year award ceremony. However, attempting to jump the Panama Canal leaves him with a sinking feeling. And even worse, his Grimbler breaks down.

episodes.name: Tower Bridge, London
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch is visiting London and spots the perfect souvenir at a riverside stall. But when he finds he has no money, he decides to raise some by working as a tour guide on the River Thames.

episodes.name: Tepui Mountains, Venezuela
episodes.overview: Foz, Kyan and Lars are climbing a Tepui in Venezuela, with Xuli exploring this amazing place in her Vroomster. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch is lost and looking for his Grimbots in the thick clouds around the Tepui. He flies up and collides with the Vroomster.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Biogas Power
episodes.overview: Glitch is excited when Lars refits the Grimbler with new, clean bio-gas boosters that could make it even faster than the Vroomster.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Hurricane Rescue
episodes.overview: Grim HQ struggles through the sky above the Atlantic Ocean, fighting against the powerful winds of a hurricane. One Grimbot falls overboard before the ship crash-lands at Go Jet Academy. Needing another ship to rescue the missing Grimbot, Glitch steals the Jetpad. The Go Jetters give chase in the Grimbler, heading right into the eye of the storm.

episodes.name: The Valley of Balls, Kazakhstan
episodes.overview: Glitch is seeking the ideal ball to use to practice his bowling - something big and heavy. Can the Go Jetters take control of a rocky situation in the Valley of Balls?

episodes.name: Gliding, Argentina
episodes.overview: The Go Jet cadets are taking to the skies in Argentina. Meanwhile, Glitch gatecrashes their academy gliding test, causing calamity in the skies.

episodes.name: Nomads, Mongolia
episodes.overview: Glitch is out on a camping expedition in Mongolia. There's not much around except a group of Mongolian nomads. He visits their camp and inadvertently offends them, then his misfiring jetpack causes him to land on one of their precious horses, causing it to gallop away from the camp with Glitch on its back.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Compass Navigators
episodes.overview: Kyan and Foz are working on their compass navigation skills and need to find the North Tower within a magnificent maze in order to pass their academy test.

episodes.name: Wolong Panda Reserve, China
episodes.overview: Lars and Foz are in the Wolong Nature Reserve in China, taking care of the 2,000 pandas that live in the wild there. Grim HQ has also landed in the Wolong reserve, having been through a monsoon. The rain has washed Grandmaster Glitch's ship sparkling clean.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Map Readers
episodes.overview: At the Go Jet Academy, Ubercorn has found an old map that leads to the GO Dome of the Ancients.

episodes.name: The Boreal Forest, Canada
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch's Grimbots really need some cuddles, so it's down to Glitch to find them a new teddy bear. Glitch knows that bears live in Ontario in Canada, so he heads there to try and find a nice cuddly bear.

episodes.name: Timgad Ruins, Algeria
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters travel to Algeria in north Africa to check out the ancient Timgad Ruins. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch's computer game controller has broken.

episodes.name: Everglades National Park, Florida
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are visiting the Everglades National Park in Florida, USA. It's an area made up mainly of water with amazing wildlife living there. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch is also at the Everglades enjoying a holiday with his Grimbots. He decides to stop and have a picnic by the water, which brings the alligators dangerously close to him and a boat full of tourists.

episodes.name: The Sphinx, Egypt
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch is in need of a holiday, so he takes his Grimbots to Egypt for some rest and relaxation. Glitch is so relaxed that he falls asleep on his deckchair in the sand. The Grimbots want to play, so decide to bury him in the sand while he sleeps. Having so much fun burying Glitch, they decide to bury the Great Sphinx, one of the oldest statues in the world.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Mudslide
episodes.overview: It's a very rainy day at the Go Jet Academy and the Go Jetters are in the training domes teaching the cadets some crucial Go Jetter skills.

episodes.name: The Great Pacific Garbage Patch
episodes.overview: A storm washes up lots of plastic litter onto the Go Jet Academy beach.

episodes.name: The Leshan Giant Buddha, China
episodes.overview: Inspired by the statue of the Giant Buddha of Leshan, Ubercorn teaches the Go Jetters all about mindfulness to help them to concentrate.

episodes.name: Kinderdijk, Netherlands
episodes.overview: It's a whirlwind of windmill excitement as the Go Jetters travel to Kinderdijk in the Netherlands to celebrate National Mill Day.

episodes.name: The Great Mosque of Djenne, Africa
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch has been invited to Djenne in Mali, Africa, to visit the people and to see one of his favorite things at work - mud.

episodes.name: Wimbledon, England
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are at Wimbledon, London, to watch the world's most famous tennis tournament. But just as they settle in to watch the doubles final, Grandmaster Glitch and his Grimbots gatecrash the court. Glitch is determined to win Wimbledon, but he is not adhering to any of the rules, and the umpire wants him to leave. But Glitch is staying put until he can play some tennis and win the tournament.

episodes.name: Cave of Crystals, Mexico
episodes.overview: While in Mexico, Glitch takes a short cut through the Cave of Crystals, a hidden space that contains some of the biggest crystals in the world. On his way through the cave the clumsy Grandmaster falls off one of the crystals and into a deep ravine.

episodes.name: Bishop Rock Lighthouse, Isles of Scilly
episodes.overview: It's a dark night and Glitch is flying his Grim HQ over the sea around the Isles of Scilly. He's in the middle of reading a bedtime story to his Grimbots when his lamp breaks. He needs a new light, and when he sees the Bishops Rock Lighthouse in the distance he demands that the Grimbots get him the bulb.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Irrigation
episodes.overview: It's farming time at the Go Jet Academy and the Go Jetters are growing corn in a big field. Their crops need watering and so the team are putting up an irrigation system which will water all the crops in the field. Growing corn is a slow process, and Grandmaster Glitch doesn't want to wait for the crops to grow. He shoots them with his size ray to make them bigger.

episodes.name: Bird Migration, Spain and Africa
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are on the Strait of Gibraltar in southern Spain, working with a team of conservationists to track and follow a group of baby storks on their journey from Spain to Africa. The storks are flying high above the sea towards Africa, but Grandmaster Glitch is also up in the air with his Grimbots working on their flying formation and nearly crashes into the migrating birds.

episodes.name: Whistler Mountain, Canada
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are on Whistler Mountain in Canada, doing some skiing and checking out the amazing cable car. Kyan and Foz are about to have a go at the Go Jet Ski Challenge when Grandmaster Glitch comes along and wants to show them how it's done - but the sneaky Grandmaster cheats by using his jet pack to power him forward. The Grimbots try to help by messing with the controls of the cable car in the control room.

episodes.name: Solar E-Glitch
episodes.overview: At the Go Jet Academy, the Go Jetters are about to watch one of nature's most spectacular events - a solar eclipse. They watch in amazement through their pinhole projectors as the moon moves between the Earth and the sun and its shadow throws them into darkness. Grandmaster Glitch has made a giant solar panel shaped like a moustache to power his Grimbots.

episodes.name: Korowai Treehouses, Indonesia
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters have been invited by the Korowai tribe to visit their village in the rainforest of Papua in Indonesia. They are an ancient tribe who build their homes above the ground. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch is also in the rainforest, trying to build the tallest treehouse in the world. When he sees that the Korowai's treehouse is even taller than his, he tries to get his even higher.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Volcanic Island
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch is drilling into the ground below the ocean near Academy Island, looking for bubbly mud that is heated up by an underground volcano. Back at the Academy, the Go Jetters have been monitoring the underground volcano and discover that it is showing more activity than usual. This is because Glitch has been drilling into it, and it could mean that the volcano is going to erupt.

episodes.name: Chocolate Hills, Philippines
episodes.overview: The Grimbots discover a place called the Chocolate Hills on Bohol Island in the Philippines and take him there. The Go Jetters are also heading to the Chocolate Hills, but when they get there they are shocked to discover that the hills are covered in real chocolate. Glitch has turned the Chocolate Hills into a chocolate theme park.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Global Gameshow
episodes.overview: It's the Go Jetters as you've never seen them before as they take part in a disco-dazzling around the world gameshow. Foz and Xuli are on Team Go Jetter and Grandmaster Glitch and Kyan are on Team Glitch as they go head to head to see who will win. Ubercorn and Lars are the quizmasters asking the questions in this ultimate geographic quiz.

episodes.name: Horsetail Fall, California
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters have travelled to Horsetail Fall in the Yosemite National Park. It's a 300m-high waterfall made of melted snow. Once a year the setting sun lights up the water, making it glow like fire for just a few special minutes. This is called Firefall, and if there isn't enough water from the melting snow, Firefall doesn't happen. Unfortunately, Grandmaster Glitch has built a snow princess at the top of the fall and is using an ice machine to stop her melting.

episodes.name: Ilulissat, Greenland
episodes.overview: Grandmaster Glitch has taken his teddy, Cuddles, to Ilulissat in Greenland to show him the sights, but Cuddles falls out of Grim HQ and gets stuck in the snow. The Grimbots melt the ice around Cuddles, and Glitch then uses Grim HQ to pull up the massive chunk of ice and carry it into the air. The Go Jetters are also in Ilulissat trying to spot some whales. They learn that Ilulissat means iceberg and that an iceberg is a huge chunk of ice which forms on land and then breaks off into the sea.

episodes.name: Sami Reindeer Herding, Norway
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are in snowy Norway to learn about the reindeer that are cared for by the local Sami people. In the spring the reindeer go on a very long journey called migration and as part of this journey they catch a ferry to take them to their warmer summer home. Grandmaster Glitch and the Grimbots are also in Norway, but their Grimbler scares the migrating reindeer and some of them run away from the herd. The Go Jetters need to keep them calm and get them back to the herd so they can finish their migration.

2.name: Series 2
2.overview:
Go Jetters Xuli, Kyan, Lars and Foz are back, and better than ever! Still travelling the world with their mentor Ubercorn, and stopping even bigger glitches than before. Grandmaster Glitch and his Grimbots have nothing on them!

The Go Jetters continue their training as cadets, now helping to do even more on the tropical island archipelago known as the Go Jet Academy. From testing brand new Click-Ons, to helping to train new cadets, the schedule for these heroes is more packed than ever before! But, even if they're at the academy, they're still learning, whether it be about natural disasters, geographical concepts, or even how certain energy is generated!

episodes.name: Honey Bee Hijack
episodes.overview:
The Go Jet Academy holds a honey contest, and while Xuli and Kyan collect honey from around the globe, Tala hopes to win despite only having a single jar. But when Glitch hatches a plan to kidnap all of the world's bees, the Go Jetters must travel across the world to stop him.

Note: This episode was aired as a 22-minutes specials.

episodes.name: Hollywood, USA
episodes.overview: After winning a part in a Hollywood film, Glitch is not happy when he has to work with Kyan to finish a scene. Meanwhile, Xuli's plans to take the perfect Hollywood photo are derailed when the Go Jetters are forced to rescue the famous Hollywood sign.

episodes.name: London Sewers Fatberg England
episodes.overview: While Xuli, Lars and Kelly go into the sewers to help keep London clean, Glitch and the Grimbots create some enormous blockages after flushing thousands of wet wipes down the toilet. It's up to the Go Jetters to clear away the fatberg Glitch has created, clean the sewers and save the city's streets.

episodes.name: Monteverde Cloud Forest, Costa Rica
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are in the Monteverde Cloud Forest, exploring the trees and hoping for a glimpse of the beautiful quetzal bird. But upset over the disintegration of his trophy duster, Glitch causes havoc when he orders his Grimbots to search for the quetzal bird's feathers. Can the Go Jetters save a rare bird's nest and find a lost trophy?

episodes.name: The Continent of Africa
episodes.overview: Glitch's plans to help Tala discover facts about Africa go wrong when they are stranded in different parts of the continent. It's up to the Go Jetters to save them from the jungles of Congo and a hippo-infested river.

episodes.name: The Continent of Europe
episodes.overview: Tala decides to focus a class project on her uncle Glitch's souvenir selfies from Europe  but little does she know that all of his pictures are atrocious. A panicking Glitch gets help from the Go Jetters, and using a series of cardboard cut-outs they start to take photos all across the continent  but can they help out when Glitch gets himself into a sticky situation?

episodes.name: Go Jetters Heroes: Polar Explorers
episodes.overview: When Kyan and Glitch race to the south pole, Glitch's loyal Grimbots steal the pole's marker to help Glitch win. But when Glitch orders them to return it, they find themselves lost and trapped in the ice  and the Go Jetters must spring into action to rescue them.

episodes.name: Middle of the World City, Ecuador
episodes.overview: After hearing about how the Monument to the Equator in Ciudad Mitad del Mundo is in the wrong location, Glitch and his Glitchbots pretend to be the Go Jetters and move the monument onto the equator. But when things start to go wrong, Glitch must learn that some glitches are fine the way they are.

episodes.name: Solar Race, Australia
episodes.overview: Glitch's hopes of winning a solar-powered race across the Australian outback are foiled when he crashes the Glitchster in the middle of the night. With the solar battery dead, Kyan and Glitch are stranded with no water and no way out. It's up to the Go Jetters to find them and save the day.

episodes.name: Go Jetters Heroes: Amelia Earhart
episodes.overview: Inspired by her hero Amelia Earhart, Xuli attempts a solo flight across the Atlantic Ocean in a vintage plane. But when accidental stowaway Tala's plans to make the engine more eco-friendly put the plane in danger, they must rely on the Go Jetters to get them out of trouble.

episodes.name: Tulip Fields, Netherlands
episodes.overview:
Xuli and Foz are in the Vroomster  but this time Foz is at the controls on a flying lesson. The pair have a rough landing in a tulip field in the Netherlands. Luckily the Vroomster doesnt have a scratch on it. Xuli and Foz are impressed with the tulip fields. Kyan, Lars and Ubercorn join over comms  it reminds Kyan of a rainbow! They all plan to meet up at the Flower Parade later.

Meanwhile Glitch is in a nearby barn, instructing the Grimbots to fetch more tulips for a giant float which looks just like Glitch! Xuli and Foz spot a Grimbot driving a harvester, which is tearing up tons of tulips and rush to the Vroomster to stop it. Xuli flies the Vroomster to the harvester and Foz jumps aboard. The Grimbot insists he has permission to cut all the flowers but Foz doesnt believe it and tries to wrestle the steering wheel from the Grimbot.

Xuli heads to the barn and discovers Glitch, Tala and Johan the flower farmer happily assembling Glitchs statue. It turns out Johan has given permission for Glitch and Tala to use the flowers to build their float  whoops! There isn't a Glitch after all and the Go Jetters have made a mistake.

Foz spots a big button in the harvester. He leans in to push it, the Grimbot notices at the last second and tries to stop him but it's too late. Foz presses the button, and both Foz and the Grimbot are ejected from the harvester and fall into a mud pile  they're stuck fast! Xuli, Glitch and Tala have run out of the barn to see the driverless harvester coming straight towards them. Xuli calls up Click Ons for her and Tala  they use G.O shield to redirect the harvester to stop it crashing into the barn. It works  but now the harvester is on course to hit the greenhouses! Xuli and Tala turn to see Glitch appear from out of the Grimbler  he has his Grim Mag on, ready to save the day. But Glitch is pulled towards the metal harvester and Xuli is dragged with them too  Grimbles!

Foz manages to free himself from the mud and flies the Vroomster to catch up with the harvester, Xuli and Glitch. After a few failed attempts Foz manages to nudge the harvester off course and away from the greenhouse; the workers are safe. But now the out of control machine is heading towards some Grimbots which are still stuck in the mud. Tala drives the float between the Grimbots and the harvester, ready to sacrifice her hard work to save her Uncle's precious Grimbots. Foz summons all his new found flying skills and manages to lift the harvester; freeing Xuli and Glitch and saving the flower float in the nick of time. With everyone saved they head to the flower parade where Foz puts his new-found driving skills to good use by driving Glitch and Talas beautiful float.

episodes.name: Himalayan Heroes, Nepal
episodes.overview: Hoping to follow in his great-aunt's footsteps, Glitch enlists the help of a sceptical Foz and a friendly yak in order to find a yeti in the Himalayas. But when a snowstorm traps them in a cave on the mountainside, the rest of the Go Jetters must battle the elements to find their friends.

episodes.name: Monkey Bay, Thailand
episodes.overview: Glitch's plans to open a hotel on an unspoilt beach in Thailand go horribly wrong when a group of macaque monkeys steal his Grim-o-freeze gun. It doesn't take long for the trouble to spread across Monkey Bay, so the Go Jetters leap into action to help save the beach, its tourists and Glitch himself.

episodes.name: Cheddar Gorge, England
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are exploring Cheddar Gorge and enjoying its rocky slopes. But Glitch, learning about the town's love of cheese, pays a visit to the gorge in order to share his fondue with the locals. This backfires horribly when he accidentally floods the gorge with the cheesy mixture. It's up to the Go Jetters to rescue the tourists, the sheep and the Grimbots  but will Foz be able to overcome his fear of heights and save a lost lamb?

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Rainbow
episodes.overview: After a rainbow appears over the Go Jet Academy, Glitch becomes fascinated with the legend of a pot of gold appearing at the end of it. He tries to create his own, bigger rainbow, ignoring Ubercorn's warnings that their ends can never be reached. When he instead causes a huge storm to appear, the Go Jetters must work fast to stop the Academy from flooding.

episodes.name: Mountain Gorillas, The Democratic Republic of the Congo
episodes.overview: When a cold-ridden Glitch's sneezing breaks his TV, the Grimbots take him to the Virunga National Park in the Democratic Republic of the Congo to see a real mountain gorilla. But Glitch doesn't realise how dangerous his cold germs can be, so the Go Jetters will have to stop him from making a baby gorilla sick  all while trying to keep it safe from dangerous traps left by hunters.

episodes.name: Go Jetters or No Jetters?
episodes.overview: After the others finish constructing the Academy bridge without him, Foz is upset; he doesn't know where he fits into the group and starts to think that he isn't needed any more. He doesn't have Xuli's ability as a pilot , Kyan's gymnastic and Lars' mechanical knowledge. But when the new bridge starts developing problems, Foz must rise to the challenge to help prevent a catastrophe.

episodes.name: Mariana Trench, the Pacific Ocean
episodes.overview: With the help of his hero Ron Allum, Lars plans to dive to the bottom of the Mariana Trench in a submersible called the Deep Sea Challenger. Glitch plans to beat him there by sending a Grimbot in his Grimsub, but it can't withstand the heavy pressure of the water. Xuli and Lars must work together to mount a rescue operation at the bottom of the sea.

episodes.name: Svalbard Global Seed Vault, Norway
episodes.overview: Ubercorn and Glitch head to the Svalbard Global Seed Vault, hoping to keep some seeds from Glitch's rare fruit tree safe for the future. But, just like when they were cadets together, the two of them get into trouble. Glitch accidentally crashes the Grimbler into the vault, and its hot engines start melting the ice that keeps the seeds cool! With the Go Jetters delayed by a malfunctioning Jet Pad, can Ubercorn and Glitch save the scientists, the vault and Glitch's rare seeds?

episodes.name: Shopping Shenanigans, Istanbul, Turkey
episodes.overview: While shopping in Istanbul's Grand Bazaar, Glitch wishes he could have some of everything. Hearing about the wishes granted by the Hen's Eye Column in an underground water store, the Basilica Cistern, Glitch heads beneath the earth. But when he gets his thumb stuck inside the column, he ends up bringing the entire cistern close to collapse! Will Foz be able to save the ancient structure without the help of click-ons?

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Sea Arch Escape
episodes.overview: When Xuli tries to beat Ubercorn's flying record, she accidentally damages a sea arch that holds up a rock formation. Inspired by Xuli's piloting skills, Tala convinces her to show her some tricks in the Grimbler, but disaster strikes when Tala traps herself under the fragile arch. The Go Jetters must race to save the day before the arch collapses.

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Ghost Crabs
episodes.overview: Glitch damages the Academy crabs' habitat when he takes all the sand from their beach.

episodes.name: Mud Volcano, Azerbaijan
episodes.overview: Lars and Glitch's plan to power their new machine with methane gas has explosive results.

episodes.name: Tomatina Festival, Bunol, Spain
episodes.overview: Can the Go Jetters fix their own 'Hlitch' at the biggest food fight in the world?

episodes.name: Go Jet Academy: Whale Rescue
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters race to the rescue when a pod of whales becomes stranded at the Academy.

episodes.name: Chinese New Year Dragon Dance Drama
episodes.overview: Even if Kyan is afraid of Chinese Dragons, he is invited to perform a dragon dance for Chinese New Year in Beijing Glitch decides to build a fire-breathing dragon robot for the parade and the Go Jetters need to stop it.

episodes.name: Holi Festival of Colour India
episodes.overview: Glitch takes all of the colourful powder from the Festival of Colour in Dwarka India

episodes.name: The Salmon Run, Alaska
episodes.overview: Alaska's a cool place to watch the salmon run, but Glitch opens a 'fishy taxi service' to help the salmon avoid tricky waterfalls and greedy bears. What could possibly go wrong?

episodes.name: Climate Change, The Arctic Ocean
episodes.overview: The Go Jetters are at the top of the world, helping Professor Wave research polar bears in the Arctic Ocean. Climate change is causing the polar bear's ice home to melt away. Although they get to see a wild polar bear called Kalik, trouble strikes when Foz and Kyan waste too much energy on heat and run down the ship's power! With a chunk of melting ice heading towards them, the Go Jetters see the perils caused by climate change first hand, and they spring into action to find a way to save the ship.

3.name: Series 3
3.overview: The Go Jetters are back, for all new adventures! Join Xuli, Kyan, Lars, Foz and new cadet Tala as they travel the world with their disco-grooving mentor, Ubercorn and foil the plans of Grandmaster Glitch and his cheeky Grimbots.
